182
00:10:37,541 --> 00:10:40,708
- Hmm? In Toledo. After the festival.
- What are you doing, Tokyo?

183
00:10:41,291 --> 00:10:42,791
TOKYO: You were drunk.

184
00:10:42,875 --> 00:10:44,750
DENVER: Fine. Fine. He was drunk.

185
00:10:44,833 --> 00:10:47,041
And you were also drunk
and so was I, okay?

186
00:10:47,125 --> 00:10:50,208
Mm, no. Actually,
Moscow ruined everything.

187
00:10:50,833 --> 00:10:52,333
Coming into the room…

188
00:10:52,916 --> 00:10:55,000
What we had together was casual.

189
00:10:56,000 --> 00:10:56,875
Anything…

190
00:10:59,291 --> 00:11:01,250
Anything could have happened back then.

191
00:11:02,541 --> 00:11:04,541
Now I'm wondering the same thing as you.

192
00:11:08,666 --> 00:11:12,583
How were we able
to stay together for so long?

193
00:11:14,041 --> 00:11:15,208
Hmm?

194
00:11:16,375 --> 00:11:18,333
(SLOW MUSIC PLAYS)

195
00:11:22,375 --> 00:11:23,250
Thank you.

196
00:11:35,833 --> 00:11:39,083
Rio, nothing happened. Nothing.

197
00:11:43,750 --> 00:11:46,291
TOKYO: <i>Love is like two people</i>
<i>on a seesaw.</i>

198
00:11:46,375 --> 00:11:48,750
<i>When one goes up, the other goes down.</i>

199
00:11:48,833 --> 00:11:51,083
<i>The balance is always fucked.</i>

200
00:11:51,166 --> 00:11:53,291
<i>Thanks to time, monotony…</i>

201
00:11:53,791 --> 00:11:55,541
<i>And sometimes, because of people like me,</i>

202
00:11:56,250 --> 00:11:58,708
<i>who only know one way</i>
<i>to get over the pain,</i>

203
00:11:59,458 --> 00:12:00,416
<i>give a little back.</i>

204
00:12:01,958 --> 00:12:04,708
PALERMO: Rio was implanted
with a microphone and GPS.

205
00:12:04,791 --> 00:12:06,416
<i>We extracted it. No problem.</i>

206
00:12:06,500 --> 00:12:08,208
Did you manage to get the chips placed?

207
00:12:08,291 --> 00:12:11,041
But of course, my dear. (CHUCKLES)

208
00:12:11,125 --> 00:12:14,916
<i>They're in a little box,</i>
<i>in a symphony of dreams.</i>

209
00:12:15,000 --> 00:12:18,916
<i>The police have been basking in a melody</i>
<i>of sleep for some time now.</i>

210
00:12:19,000 --> 00:12:20,958
(SNORING OVER SPEAKER)

211
00:12:22,375 --> 00:12:24,166
(SNORING OVER FEED)

212
00:12:29,666 --> 00:12:33,208
PROFESSOR: <i>It's time</i>
<i>to give them something more. Palermo.</i>

213
00:12:34,708 --> 00:12:36,291
It's time for Plan Alcatraz.

214
00:12:37,041 --> 00:12:38,458
<i>Initiate as soon as possible.</i>

215
00:12:40,791 --> 00:12:42,041
Plan Alcatraz?

216
00:12:42,791 --> 00:12:45,250
<i>Sergio, what the fuck</i>
<i>is going on out there?</i>

217
00:12:46,375 --> 00:12:47,750
Our situation

218
00:12:48,458 --> 00:12:49,541
is extreme.

219
00:12:57,416 --> 00:12:59,791
Lisbon and I may be faced
with pressure at some point

220
00:12:59,875 --> 00:13:02,166
that we won't be able
to handle by ourselves.

221
00:13:02,708 --> 00:13:05,625
We'll have the army on top of us.
The police.

222
00:13:06,583 --> 00:13:08,458
And some things may go wrong.

223
00:13:08,541 --> 00:13:09,666
But that's why

224
00:13:10,625 --> 00:13:12,083
we have Plan Alcatraz.

225
00:13:12,708 --> 00:13:15,833
If Lisbon and I find ourselves
in a critical situation,

226
00:13:15,916 --> 00:13:18,791
we'll need you to create
the largest diversion possible.

227
00:13:18,875 --> 00:13:21,083
LISBON: The objective is
for the police to be looking

228
00:13:21,166 --> 00:13:22,833
at two places at the same time.

229
00:13:22,916 --> 00:13:26,541
And there's only one thing more powerful
than capturing the two of us.

230
00:13:27,333 --> 00:13:28,500
Capturing all of us?

231
00:13:30,541 --> 00:13:32,083
If all of you were to escape,

232
00:13:32,166 --> 00:13:34,833
that would be
the biggest distraction we could create.

233
00:13:36,500 --> 00:13:38,125
This will drive them crazy.

234
